    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
            <opener><dateline><date when="1912-09-30">Sep. 30, 1912</dateline></date>
                <salute>My dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Miss Monroe</persName>-</salute></opener>
            <p>The first number of "<title key="poetry" key="j">Poetry</title>" has come, and may I compliment you upon it? It is
               exceedingly interesting and to have such a magazine is a most cheering thing to all who care for poetry, and for us
               who are trying to make it, to know that there is an editor who really knows and feels, does make a very
               great difference.</p>
            <p>This copy which I have received lacks pp 5 to 12 inclusive, so may I ask for another copy?
            <p>As you say in this number that you are going to review books of poetry, I have asked Messrs <orgName key="houghton_mifflin">Houghton Mifflin &mp; Co.</orgName>
               to send you my forthcoming volume.</p>
            <p>With every good wish for what you have so inspiringly begun</p>
            <closer>Sincerely yours</closer>    
        </body>
    </text>
